## Ship pipeline (Desktop = Cloud)

Production reaches **Cloudflare Pages only when a PR merges to `main`**. Direct push to `main` is blocked.

| Step | Desktop (Cursor / VS Code) | Cloud agent |
|------|------------------------------|-------------|
| 1 | `git checkout main && git pull` | same |
| 2 | Branch `cursor/<description>-fb87` | same |
| 3 | Edit, smoke check, bump versions | same |
| 4 | `.\scripts\deploy.ps1` or Run Task **Ship** | commit, push, open PR |
| 5 | Auto-merge when Cloudflare Pages passes | same workflow |
| 6 | Pull `main`; refresh SPA; reload extension if needed | user pulls locally |

Draft PRs from Cloud/Android agents are **auto-promoted** by `.github/workflows/auto-merge-cursor.yml` (REST/GraphQL undraft — no `gh` CLI in CI). A **15-minute cron sweep** retries any stuck draft `cursor/*` PRs once Cloudflare Pages is green.

`deploy.ps1` / `push.ps1`: commit → push branch (never `main`) → open PR via `gh` → `.github/workflows/auto-merge-cursor.yml` squash-merges.

### Stuck deploy (Cloudflare not updating)

Production only changes when a **cursor/\* PR merges to `main`**. If a PR is open but Cloudflare is stale:

1. Open the PR on GitHub — confirm **Cloudflare Pages** check is green.
2. Auto-merge promotes **draft** `cursor/*` PRs via GitHub API (REST then GraphQL). A cron job re-runs every 15 minutes for stuck drafts or green-but-unmerged PRs.
3. Manual recovery: Actions → **Auto-merge cursor agent PRs** → Run workflow → optional `pr_number`.
4. After merge: pull `main`, hard-refresh https://househunt.pages.dev; reload extension only if `extension/` changed.

**Note:** The old `gh pr ready` shell step failed in CI (`fatal: not a git repository`) — replaced with API-based undraft in the workflow.

**On `main` with local changes:** pass `-Description 'my-feature'` to create `cursor/my-feature-fb87`.

